<HEADLINE> Top Army Leaders Attend Concert On HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- General Liu Huaqing, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee and Vice-Chairman of the Central
Military Commission (CMC), joined more than 1,000 people at a
concert here this evening, marking the upcoming return of Hong
Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
CMC vice-chairmen Zhang Zhen, Zhang Wannian and Chi Haotian
and CMC members Fu Quanyou, Yu Yongbo and Wang Ke were also among
the 1,000-plus listeners. The concert is said to be the largest
ever art performance by army troupes.
</P>
<P>
The first chapter of the concert tells about the glorious
experiences of the Chinese nation who have fought for the national
independence and reunification and praised the late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping for his creation of the concept of "one country, two
systems".
</P>
<P>
The second chapter shows the confidence of the People's
Liberation Army to safeguard the country including Hong Kong, and
the third chapter praises the current reform and opening-up and
and expresses the determination of the Chinese people rallying
around the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the
core. 
</P>
</TEXT>
