<HEADLINE> Thailand to Set Up Special Visa Center for Foreign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet today approved
the establishment of a special center in Bangkok to provide quick
visa and work permit services for foreign investors in a bid to
attract foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The center will provide one-stop service to foreign investors
on the issuance of visa and work permit within three hours, the
Thai Government House said.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners who invest not less than 2 million baht ( 80,000 US
dollars) will be qualified for a one-year visa and work permit.
Those who invest not less than 10 million baht (400,000 dollars)
will be qualified for a two-year permit at the center.  
</P>
</TEXT>
