<HEADLINE> NATO Enlargement Creates New Division in Europe, says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The German opposition Greens Party
today warned that the planned eastward expansion of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) would create new military and
political divisions in Europe.
</P>
<P>
"Disarmament and the swift opening of the European Union is
what is needed... not the expansion of NATO linked to a
militarisation of EU foreign policy," said the Greens in a
declaration quoted by the German DPA news agency Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
NATO expansion would waste a chance to overcome the legacy of
Cold War bloc confrontation and could lead to a new division in
Europe, said the Greens, Germany's third biggest political party
after Chancellor Helmut Kohl's Christian Democratic Union and the
main opposition Social Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
It also called for the strengthening of the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE), instead of the NATO.
</P>
<P>
NATO leaders are due to meet in Madrid on July 8-9 when they
are expected to decide on which eastern European countries would
be invited to join the western military alliance.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic, Hungary and Poland are widely expected to
be the candidates to join in the first wave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
