<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Ratifies U.N. Anti-Desertification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 24 (Xinhua) --Ethiopia's parliament, the House
of People's Representatives, today endorsed the United
Nations convention on combating desertification which provides a
framework for sustainable development in dry-lands.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the house unanimously
endorsed the convention at a regular session with a strong
belief that the convention enhances measures taken by the government to
contain land degradation and drought in addition to fostering
access to financial resources and technologies from international
organizations and the developed world.
</P>
<P>
Desertification is strictly defined as land degradation in
arid, semi-arid and dry sub-humid areas. Ethiopia with 60-70
percent of its land within this category, was active during the
negotiations of the convention and was one of the first to sign
it, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia signed the convention in October 1994 at the Paris
conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
