<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, India Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Chamber of
Commerce and the Indian Joint Business Council today signed an
agreement to promote trade and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to the document, India is entitled to display its
products at trade fairs in Ethiopia and is committed to offering
training to members of the Ethiopian Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Chamber of Commerce will facilitate conditions
to Indian investors willing to open businesses here. Delegations
of both sides will also pay visits to each other country so as to
share experiences, the document said.
</P>
