<HEADLINE> Killing of Aid Worker Condemned in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The self-styled Somali
government of Hussein Mohamed Aidid has strongly condemned the
attack and killing of a Portuguese aid worker killed in Baidoa
four days ago.
</P>
<P>
A statement broadcast last night at Radio South Mogadishu
supporting Hussein Mohamed Aidid said that an investigation
is going on over the killing of Riccardo Marques from the
MSF-Portugal, who was shot dead by unidentified gunmen in Baidoa
Hospital, 245 km southwest of Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The radio said that ome suspect has been apprehended and will
be put before the court after the investigation is concluded.
</P>
<P>
The killing was also condemned by the Rahanwein Resistance
Army (RRA) fighting against Hussein Mohamed Aidid in Bay and
Bakol regions of southwestern Somalia. Ali Aden Margus, the
political leader of RRA has accused Hussein Aidid's men for
carrying out the killing.
</P>
<P>
Marques, a gynecologist doctor, was killed by gunmen while on
duty in Baidoa Hospital on Friday. According to independent
sources, the killing was related to employment dispute between
MST-Portugal and the gunmen in the town which is controlled by
the sopporters of Hussein Mohamed Aidid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
