<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish President: Hong Kong's Return to China Is </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel
said here today that China's resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong will be a great achievement of China
and also a "world example."
</P>
<P>
Demirel made the remarks at a meeting with outgoing Chinese
Ambassador to Turkey Wu Keming at the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
He said that Hong Kong serves as a gateway of China and
maintaining stability and development in Hong Kong is very
beneficial to both China and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
On the bilateral relations, the Turkish president said, "
There exist no political problems between Turkey and China,"
adding that the two governments should encourage investment in
each other's country.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president said Turkey is willing to cooperate with
China to revive the "Silk Road" by opening up a railway from
Beijing to London. 
</P>
</TEXT>
