<HEADLINE> Assassination Plot Exposed in Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Eritrean government has
accused the Sudanese government of plotting to assassinate its
President Isaias Afwerki.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued on Tuesday, the Eritrean Foreign
Ministry said that the Sudanese government "plotted to assassinate
President Isaias Afwerki, dispatching a member of its foreign
security forces to Eritrea on November 14, 1996" to infiltrate the
National Democratic Alliance of the Sudan, which operated in Eritrea,
"to accomplish the abominable act".
</P>
<P>
The ministry said, "The heinous crime was conceived at the
highest level with explicit operational orders given to the
terrorist from senior government officials".
</P>
<P>
It pointed out, the assassination mission in Eritrea was
planned to "be executed by Captain Al Khairat alone although other
subversive support groups were also dispatched from Khartoum at
the same time".
</P>
<P>
In addition to a detailed information on the plot to assassinate
President Isaias, Captain Al Khairat has further confirmed
"subversive and terrorist sponsoring activities", it added.
</P>
<P>
The assassin had confessed that the primary motive behind the
assassination plot was to bring about political confusion in
Eritrea, the press release said. The Eritrean Foreign Ministry
called upon the international community to " take immediate and
appropriate action against the Sudanese government to ensure the
cessation of these illicit acts". 
</P>
</TEXT>
