government to visit the Gulf region. Before his Gulf trip, he had
visited Israel, Egypt, Lebanon and Syria since he took office
last month.
</P>
<P>
Western Diplomats said that his Gulf tour is an indication of
the high priority placed by the British Labor government on links
with the Gulf states which include Oman, the United Arab
Emirates, Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, Qatar and Bahrain.
</P>
<P>
