<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Shares Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 24 (Xinhua) - All shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended higher today.
</P>
<P>
Britain's leading share index snapped out of a six-day losing
streak as bid speculation, coupled with a solid rebound on Wall
Street. The FTSE-100 closed at 4,596.3, up 20.5 points.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, shares took their lead from a rebound on Wall
Street in late afternoon European trade to post modest gains. The
DAX-30 index closed at 3,755.82, up 1.10 points.
</P>
<P>
French stocks ended an extremely active session higher,
bolstered by a turnaround on Wall Street and firmer European bond
prices. The CAC-40 index closed at 2,784.76, up 22.56 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
