<HEADLINE> Netanyahu Survives No-confidence Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu's government today survived a no-confidence vote in the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Opposition's motion was quelled by a 55-50 vote with two
abstentions in the 120-member Knesset.
</P>
<P>
The motion was introduced after several cabinet members claimed
that they did not trust Netanyahu and boycotted cabinet meetings.
</P>
<P>
After tiding over the crisis, Netanyahu said "I am very happy"
with the result of the vote.
</P>
<P>
Opposition Labor leader Ehud Barak claimed partial victory,
saying today's no-confidence vote is the beginning of the collapse
of Netanyahu's government. 
</P>
