<HEADLINE> Angola to Invest US$10 million in Restoring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government will invest
10 million US Dollars to restore its traditional agricultural
production.
</P>
<P>
The decision was disclosed by the Angolan Ministry of
Agriculture today in Huambo, a central Angolan city, reported the
local press.
</P>
<P>
As the country regains peace and stability, restoration of
agricultural production is required to solve the problem of
food shortages and to further provide raw materials for
the processing industry, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministry also decided to earmark 30 million
US Dollars for restoring the country's rural trade network in 10
of its 18 provinces, as a major step to boost trade in and
transport of agricultural products, according to the report.
</P>
