<HEADLINE> France Beats Mexico on Luccin's Last-minute Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 25 (Xinhua) -- France edged Mexico 1-0
thanks to a last-minute goal by Peter Luccin, booking a
quarter-final berth in the world youth football championships here
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
France will play Uruguay, 3-0 winners over the United States,
in Sunday's quarter-finals at Shah Alam stadium on the outskirts
of Kuala Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's plan to block the dangerous French strikers, David
Trezeget and captain Thierry Henry, worked well as the European
champions found few opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The unmarked Luccin swooped on a loose ball in the dying time
and beat Mexican goalkeeper Alejandro Alvares with a powerful shot.
</P>
<P>
It was the second straight win for France over Mexico after
their 2-1 success at the Toulan international earlier this month.
</P>
