<HEADLINE> HK Launches Narcotics Division Homepage against Drug Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's anti-drug messages
will be brought into the schools and homes of young persons
locally and internationally via a homepage on the Internet on the
International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner for Narcotics Clarie Lo said here today that Hong
Kong is and will continue to be a strong supporter of
international actions to fight against drugs.
</P>
<P>
She said, "We choose June 26 to launch the Homepage to
commemorate the International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit
Trafficking."
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Government Narcotics Division Homepage on the
worldwide web is one of Hong Kong's new strategies to steer young
people away from drugs.
</P>
<P>
With the aid of color photographs and graphic illustrations,
the Homepage is divided into nine sections:
</P>
<P>
Anti-drug strategy, drug information, drug statistics,
anti-drug laws and law enforcement, preventive education and
publicity, treatment and rehabilitation, international
cooperation, beat drugs fund and publications.
</P>
<P>
Lo said the preventive education and publicity section of the
Homepage explains common factors leading to drug abuse, ways on
how to "say no to drugs," and substances liable to abuse as well
as their harmful effects.
</P>
<P>
She said that it also provides information on how to handle
drug abuse by youngsters and supportive services provided by
various government departments and voluntary agencies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
