<DOCNO> XIE19970625.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Balanced Budget, Key to HK's Economic Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, the 45-year-old secretary said he
is resolved to continue implementing this fiscal policy as
stipulated in the Basic Law, so as to build up a sound base for
the long-term prosperity of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to Kwong, the Hong Kong government has always attached
great importance to its effort to keep a balanced budget.
</P>
<P>
As the growth in revenue has kept abreast of the economic
growth, Hong Kong usually works out its annual budget in
accordance with the five-year economic growth forecast and the
relevant anticipated revenue augment.
</P>
<P>
The arrangements for the expenditure are also based on the
principle that the expenditure growth shall not exceed the
economic growth rate in term of a five-year period.
</P>
<P>
In order to strive for a balanced budget, which often
constitutes no easy job, a tight control on the expenditure is
always essential, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
For the sake of attaining this objective, he added, it is
helpful and beneficial to solicit people's views extensively from
all walks of life and to keep in good communication with the
related departments so as to win support from society at large.
</P>
<P>
In his view, the fiscal and taxation policies as stipulated in
the Basic Law are in conformity with the consistent financial
policies of Hong Kong, and these policies will remain the same
after Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's economy has kept growing yearly ever since 1962.
"As long as the continuity of the policies is ensured, the
long-term development of Hong Kong will be guaranteed," the
secretary for treasury assured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
