<HEADLINE> Chinese Power Plant Gets Large Foreign Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Hefei No. 2 Power Plant, in
the capital of east China's Anhui Province, has got 235.8
million US dollars worth of foreign bank loans for new generating
units, representing a new means of applying foreign funds to the
power industry.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo attended a signing ceremony today in
Beijing's Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the loans from a German bank and a Singaporean
bank, China's State Development Bank and the China Construction
Bank will provide 1.528 billion yuan in loans.
</P>
<P>
The plant is designed to have two 350,000-kw generating units
in the first phase, at a cost of 4.639 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
When the first phase is completed by the year 2000, its annual
power output will reach four billion kwh. The construction of the
project will start this year.
</P>
<P>
Major equipment will be provided by the ABB group of Germany,
and boilers will be made by the Harbin Boiler Plant.  
</P>
</TEXT>
