<HEADLINE> Tibetan Hydro-electric Power Plant Begins Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The first generating unit of Yamzho
Yumco Hydro-electric Power Station, the largest station of its
kind in the Tibetan Autonomous Region, began producing electricity
today after a three-day trial operation,
</P>
<P>
The power plant was a state key project for the Eighth
Five-Year Plan and was meant to boost Tibetan economic development
and improve local people's lives.
</P>
<P>
Installed with four Austrian generating units, the station is
designed to have a total capacity of 112,500 kw. The first unit
supplies 10,000 kw of electricity to the Tibetan grid.
</P>
<P>
The other three will be ready for operation by the end of the
year.  
</P>
