<HEADLINE> Kinkel Says Germany Confident in Hong Kong's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
said today he was confident of Hong Kong's future after its return
to China on July 1 and he believed the now excellent Sino-German
relations would continue.
</P>
<P>
"I am convinced that, on the basis of the 1984 Sino-British
Joint Declaration and the Basic Law for the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, Hong Kong will thrive and prosper" after it
returns to China and it will continue the impressive development
it has experienced over the past decades, Kinkel said in an
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
