Kong today, we see bright prospects ahead. German companies have
every confidence in Hong Kong's future."
</P>
<P>
Kinkel said that he himself will be traveling to Hong Kong to
represent Germany at the handover ceremonies. He said: "This is a
historic event which the whole world will be watching with great
interest."
</P>
<P>
He also praised the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's concept
of "one country, two systems", saying "his concept makes good
political sense. It takes into account that conditions in Hong
Kong are different from those prevailing elsewhere in the People's
Republic of China."
</P>
<P>
"It is our understanding that the concept developed by Deng
Xiaoping will be implemented in the form that has been agreed. On
this basis Hong Kong will continue to flourish," he said.
