<HEADLINE> France Books Quarterfinal Berth in Youth Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 25 (Xinhua) -- One last minute goal from
Peter Luccin helped France to beat Mexico 1-0 and advance to the
quarter-finals at the world youth football championships here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
France was joined by Uruguay, Brazil and Ireland in the
quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
France, the European Under-18 champion, scored the sole goal
through Peter Luccin at the last minute of the match against
Mexico who are out of contention even though displaying an
impressive game.
</P>
<P>
In the quarter-finals, France will meet Uruguay who edged the
United States 3-0 in a second round of the World Youth Cup Finals
at the Shah Alam Stadium earlier.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay scored three goals in the first half in a match they
dominated after the kick-off.
</P>
<P>
In the other match in Sarawak Stadium, Brazil also cruised into
the quarter-finals in style when they crushed Belgium 10-0.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, who hammered South Korea 10-3 last Sunday, repeated
their feat in a similar fashion with total domination, leaving the
Belgians no chance at all to launch decent shots.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, in search of a fourth title, will meet the winner
between arch-rival defending champions Argentina or England.
</P>
<P>
Ireland qualified for the quarterfinals by beating Morocco 2-1
with a golden ball in the extra time.
</P>
<P>
Ireland and Morocco were tied 1-1 at halftime with Ireland's
Neale Fenn opening the scoring in the 33rd minute. But his
teammate David Worrall scored an own goal in the 42nd to make it
1-1.
</P>
<P>
During the extra time, Ireland's Damien Duff net the decisive
goal at the 95th minute.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, another four second round matches will be played
with Ghana taking on the United Arab Emirates, Spain meeting
Canada, Australia facing Japan and England challenging Argentina.
</P>
</TEXT>
