<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition on Hong Kong Opens in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A photo exhibition opened here
today to celebrate China's resumption of its exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Through about 150 photos, the show depicts the history of Hong
Kong, the evolution of the Hong Kong question, efforts by the
Chinese government to recover Hong Kong and a bright future for
the region.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony at the Philippine National
Library, Guan Dengming, Chinese ambassador to the Philippines,
said the show was organized to "enable our Filipino friends to
have a better understanding about Hong Kong's history, present
situation and its beautiful future."
</P>
<P>
"After resuming its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong,"
Guan said, "the Chinese government will strictly abide by the
Basic Law of Hong Kong and genuinely practice the principles of
'one country, two systems', Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong
and a 'high degree of autonomy' so as to ensure long lasting
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
The 10-day exhibition, entitled "A Brighter Future for Hong
Kong," was sponsored by the Chinese embassy in cooperation with
the Federation of Filipino-Chinese Association of the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
A documentary film on Hong Kong's history over the past
century was shown after the opening ceremony, which was attended
by more than 600 people, including some Philippine government
officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
