<HEADLINE> Snooker Star Jailed for Drug Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Snooker star Silvino Francisco has
been jailed for three years for smuggling 47 kilograms of cannabis
into Britain, reports reaching here said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
South-African born Francisco, 50, was found guilty to smuggling
155,000 pounds (about 250,000 U.S. dollars) worth of the drug
through the port of Dover on February 10 this year.
</P>
<P>
Customs officers stopped the former British Open champion as he
left a ferry and found the cannabis resin hidden in his Fiat
sports car.
</P>
<P>
Once ranked in the top ten of world snooker players, Francisco
was declared bankrupt last year and is now outside the top 100.
