<HEADLINE> HK and Macao Affairs Office Spokesman On HK Legal Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman from the Hong Kong and
Macao Affairs Office of the State Council today commented on some
ordinances passed in great haste by the Legislative Council of the
British Hong Kong authorities in recent days.
</P>
<P>
In an interview, spokesman said that the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress adopted a decision on handling the
existing laws of Hong Kong in accordance with Article 160 of the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) on
February 23 of this year. Afterwards, the British Hong Kong
authorities unilaterally and significantly amended the existing
Hong Kong laws that the NPC Standing Committee announced would be
adopted by the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
In response, the Office of the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
SAR announced that the office will deal with these amendments on
the existing Hong Kong laws.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman voiced his approval of the Chief Executive
Office's decision, saying that this move will help safeguard the
Basic Law and relevant decisions of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
