<HEADLINE> Portugal Says Macao Can Learn From Smooth Hong Kong Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio
said here today that Hong Kong's smooth transition will have a
positive influence on Macao.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Sampaio said Hong Kong's
continuing stability and prosperity after the July 1 handover will
be an encouragement for Macao before its own return to China in
1999.
</P>
<P>
He said that he was optimistic about Hong Kong's future and
believed the efforts China and Britain made for Hong Kong's smooth
transition will pay off.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese president added that Hong Kong's return to China
is an event of global significance and the whole world will be
watching with great interest.
</P>
<P>
He praised the "one country, two systems" concept initiated by
the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, saying it is a pragmatic
and wise way to handle the issues of Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The concept takes into account the actual circumstances of the
two regions and the interests of their citizens, while trying to
guarantee a smooth transfer of power, Sampaio said.
</P>
<P>
He said China and Portugal have both committed themselves to a
smooth transition of Macao and to handling the transfer of power
in a way beneficial to bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
It is very important for the interests of Macao and its
citizens that China and Portugal both respect the spirit of
responsibility and cooperation shown in the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration on the Question of Macao, said Sampaio.
</P>
<P>
He added that he hoped China and Portugal will continue to
cooperate over Macao's transition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
