<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Carry Out Nation-wide Anti-Dengue Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A one-month long anti-dengue
campaign will be carried out soon throughout Malaysia to contain
the mosquito-borne disease which has so far claimed 34 lives in
the country since last year.
</P>
<P>
Housing and Local Government Minister Ting Chew Peh said today
from now on his ministry will spearhead preventive efforts to
check the breeding of aedes mosquitoes, which cause the disease.
</P>
<P>
The health, finance, education, home affairs and human
resources ministries and local authorities would also be involved,
he told reporters after chairing the ministry's post-cabinet
meeting here.
</P>
<P>
He said his ministry will discuss with the other ministries in
a day or two details of the proposed campaign and other preventive
measures.
</P>
<P>
Ting has instructed local authorities to draw up regulations
requiring all developers to form anti-dengue groups comprising
their own staff.
</P>
<P>
"The authorities are also asked to impose Aedes-free condition
on developers before approving their building plans," Ting said.
</P>
