<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Regulations On Chinese Citizens Travelling Abroad (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A set of provisional regulations
on Chinese citizens travelling abroad at their own expense was
issued by the Chinese government today, and will take effect July
1.
</P>
<P>
The regulation, which was drawn up by the China National
Tourism Administration (CNTA) and the Ministry of Public Security
and was approved by the State Council, is the first of its kind.
</P>
<P>
They say that expenses that formerly had to be covered by
overseas relatives can now be paid by Chinese citizens themselves,
and that the type of travel referred to as a tour group must have
at least three people.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, after tourists headed abroad have paid their
travel expenses at a travel agency, they should apply to the
public security department where they reside with requisite
certificates, including identification card and verification
certificate from the local tourism administrations.
</P>
<P>
After that, the public security department will, within 20
days, decide whether to approve or deny the request in accordance
with the law. Travelers should exit and enter China only through
ports of entry where border checks are made.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970625.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> About 150 Rebels Killed in North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- About 150 Tamil rebels were killed
early this morning when they launched a major attack on the
government troops-controlled areas in Northern province, according
to a military spokesman this evening.
</P>
<P>
The rebels had concentrated their main effort on the 122 mm
artillery position and 120 mm mortar position. Concurrently, the
rebels engaged the troops from the western flank with machine guns
and mortar fire.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated effectively killing around 150 and
injuring a large number of others. The rebels withdrew northward
from the area in the face of heavy retaliatory attacks by the
troops, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said four officers and over 60 soldiers were killed
and 68 soldiers were injured in action.
</P>
<P>
The latest round of Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain Victory) was
launched by government troops on May 13 to open a key supply line
along a highway linking Vavuniya to the Jaffna Peninsula.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
