<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Regulations on Chinese Citizens Travelling Abroad (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The regulations state the extent of operations and standards of
tourism departments and public security and their
responsibilities, and the responsibilities, obligations, and
rights of the travelers going abroad. They also state the
responsiblities and obligations of international travel agencies
that are approved for overseas travel, and penalties for
misconduct.
</P>
<P>
He Guangwei, director-general of CNTA, said that the National
Tourism Administration will check the travel agencies for approval
in accordance with the Regulations on the Management of Travel
Agencies and by examining the performance of the travel
agencies. The number of these travel agencies will soon climb to
67 from the current 9.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are now only four approved destinations for
travel abroad: Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
"But CNTA will propose more destinations with the ministries of
Foreign Affairs and Public Security, and apply for approval by the
State Council," he said, pointing out that management principles
for overseas travel are meant to develop it in an organized,
planned, and controled manner.
</P>
</TEXT>
