<HEADLINE> HK Welcomes U.S. Renewal of China MFN Trading Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Denise Yue, secretary for Trade
and Industry of the Hong Kong government, today welcomed the U.S.
House of Representatives' vote for the renewal of China's Most
Favored Nation (MFN) trading status this year.
</P>
<P>
Yue said, " We are very pleased with the result. The renewal
of China's MFN status always matters greatly to Hong Kong, but it
has never mattered more than this year when Hong Kong will embark
on a new chapter in its history in less than a week's time."
</P>
<P>
She said that the renewal of China's MFN status goes a long way
to ensure the continued economic vibrancy of Hong Kong during the
handover period.
</P>
<P>
She noted that economic strength is vitally important as Hong
Kong settles into the new relationship of being a Special
Administrative Region of China, enjoying a high degree of autonomy
in its government, legal system, civil service and trade and
economic affairs.
</P>
<P>
With the unconditional renewal of China's MFN status, American
companies will continue to find Hong Kong a good place to do
business in Asia, she added.
</P>
<P>
On June 24, the House of Representatives of the United States
rejected an attempt to disapprove the President's decision to
extend China's MFN status for another year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
