<HEADLINE> hkhk- Work Report on Hong Kong's Sewage Disposal scheme Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Signed by representatives of the Sino-British Sewage Disposal
Technical Sub-group (SDTSG), the report will be submitted to the
Hong Kong Sewage Disposal Expert Group (SDEG) of the Sino-British
Joint Liaison Group (JLG) for examination.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement reached between the Chinese and
British sides, Chinese and British experts of SDTSG, which is
under SDEG, over the past one year has held consultations on the
work concerning assessment of the impact of a strategic sewage
disposal scheme on the environment.
</P>
<P>
According to experts, the assessment is designed to set
standards for marine environment for the strategic sewage disposal
scheme, choose ideal outfalls, draw up a long-term plan for sewage
treatment and disposal, and assess the possible impact of such a
plan on the overall environment.
</P>
<P>
The Environmental Protection Department has entrusted two
companies, the Binhai Waster Water Treatment and Disposal (HK)
Consultants Ltd. and the Montgomery Watts HK Ltd., to undertake
the assessment, which is scheduled for completion in August, 1998.
</P>
