<HEADLINE> Lufthansa Continues to Expand Regional Alliances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The German airline Deutsche Lufthansa
will soon conclude a deal on cooperation with the northern Belgian
air carrier VLM, in further efforts to expand its network of
regional alliances, said reports reaching here today from
Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
Lufthansa said that its deal with the Antwerpen-based Vlaamse
Luchttransport Maatschappij (VLM) was the 21st of the kind. Under
the accord, the company will enter code-sharing services on 104
flights to be jointly offered with VLM weekly beginning July 1.
</P>
<P>
VLM currently flies such short-distance routes as from
Antwerpen to Rotterdam, Moenchengladbach and London.
</P>
<P>
VLM was set up in 1992 and has now a fleet of six airplanes. It
expects to transport 200,000 passengers this year, up from about
150,000 passengers in 1996. 
