<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Says Priority Should Be Given To Market Studies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua, on a visit
to Fujian Province in east China from June 21 to 25, said that
market studies should be made for developing the economy and that
an effort must be made to speed up capital turnover and increase
revenues.
</P>
