demand to increase national strength, productivity, and to improve
living standards, the Vice-Premier said, noting that the market
must be followed in improving the production-sales ratio and
market share.
</P>
<P>
Attention should also be paid to balancing infrastructure and
other industries, and speeding up capital accumulation to improve
infrastructure, by developing short-term but high-efficient
projects, such as the light industry, Zou said. 
