<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Busy Preparing for Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- People from all walks of life in
Hong Kong are busy preparing to celebrate Hong Kong's return to
China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
A large evening show, organized by the Committee for Activities
to Mark Hong Kong's Return to the Motherland by Various Sectors in
Hong Kong, will be staged in the Hung Hom Stadium in Kowloon on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
According to an engineering consultant to the show, the
erection of a stage 127 meters long and 76 meters wide is nearly
complete after five days of work, and 800 ceiling lights will be
installed. Famous domestic and overseas actors and actresses will
perform during the show.
</P>
<P>
A preparatory committee for activities to mark Hong Kong's
return by the industrial and commercial community in Hong Kong
will sponsor a large floats parade on July 2.
</P>
<P>
The 31 floats will represent the good wishes for Hong Kong from
the 31 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
