<HEADLINE> Japan Beats Nepal in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Japan kept their winning streak
intact in the World Cup premilinaries after beating
Nepal 3-0 here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese team collected 15 points from the five wins in
Asian zone Group Four, three points ahead of nearest rivals Oman,
a 2-0 win over Macau earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
On the final day on Sunday, Oman will have to beat Japan by
10-0 for a better goal differential to advance to the next
qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
Forward Akinori Nishizawa scored on a rebound in the 44th
minute after Nepal keeper Upendra Man Singh fumbled the ball on a
right corner.
</P>
<P>
Ace striker Kazuyoshi Miura, who was severely checked by
defender Dev Narayan Chawdhary, made it 2-0 when he was given a
free kick chance in the 72nd minute from just outside of the area.
</P>
<P>
In the 87th minute, Nishizawa produced a straight pass to Miura
in the area for an insurance goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
