<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices were mixed on the
Singapore market, while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index fell by 17.52 points to close at 2023.86 points today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume increased further to 163.23 million units,
valued at 365.96 million Singapore dollars (about 255.92 million
US dollars). Advances overtook declines by 214 to 112, while 296
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Van Der Horst was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 25.38 million units. It was followed by
Tye Soon which had 11.89 million shares traded. Ber Industry was
next with 7.19 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign and NBT shared
the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them rose by 50 cents
to finish at 18.5 and 20.7 Singapore dollars respectively. City
Developments increased by 40 cents to end at 14 Singapore dollars,
while Van Der Warrant 98 closed 36 cents higher at 1.81 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50, GE Life, and Malaya Banking were
the biggest losers as each of them declined by 60 cents to end at
23.4, 17.2 and 14.5 dollars respectively. Local car distributor
Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) fell by 30 cents to close at 14.8 Singapore
dollars, while SGM finished 27 cents lower at 0.83 Hong Kong
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
