<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims Lives in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Several people have died in the
far north province of Kameroun while another cholera outbreak
took place in recent days, local radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
Reports say hygienic conditions are getting worse as the rainy
season is going on. Cameroun's health department has taken some
necessary measures to prevent further spreading of the illness.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the illness caused more than 500 people to die in
that part of the country at the same time.
</P>
<P>
Cholera is an illness which for now has no vaccine in Cameroun
but which can be avoided by simply respecting common rules of
elementary hygiene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
