<HEADLINE> Cameroun to Start New Car Insurance Certificate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A new car insurance certificate
will go operational in Cameroun from July 1, 1997, local radio
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The new insurance certificate in line with the reforms toward
a new insurance policy is designed by the National Association of
Insurance Companies of Cameroun in collaboration with 13 African
countries.
</P>
<P>
The new car insurance certificate which is in the form of car
stickers features butterflies in water mark as its logo and has
yellow as its predominant color.
</P>
<P>
The new certificate will carry among other things the full
identity of the car owner, the registration number of the vehicle
as well as the duration of the policy.
</P>
<P>
The new certificate has other security devices which can not
be seen with naked eyes. It is aimed at tracking down false
certificates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
