<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Speed Up Development of "Mega-forestry" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A senior leader in China's highest
legislature today urged that closer attention be paid to the
development of the forestry industry.
</P>
<P>
The call from Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee of National People's Congress (NPC), was made at a
meeting on the inspection of law enforcement for forests. Wang
said that forestry plays an important role in China's national
economy, social and environmental development, and he urged
development in the sector under the concept of " mega-forestry".
</P>
<P>
"Forestry is not only the production of timber and conservation
-- its influence can be felt in many areas including the economy,
society, ecology and natural resources," he said.
</P>
<P>
Three groups were sent by the NPC Standing Committee to
Jiangxi, Fujian and Yunnan provinces last April to check up on
forest law enforcements. They visited timber production areas,
nature reserves, afforestation areas, forest parks and gardens,
markets, enterprises and individual farmers.
</P>
<P>
Wang spoke highly of the achievements local governments have
made in implementing the Forestry Law. In Fujian and Jiangxi, all
waste hilly land has been planted with trees and grass. Forest
coverage rate in the two provinces has increased to 57 percent and
52 percent respectively, far in excess of the national average,
13.92 percent.
</P>
<P>
In Yunnan, a total 87 nature reserves for the protection of
trees and wildlife have been established. They form part of a
national network which protects 67.5 percent of the country's
plant and animal species.
</P>
<P>
However, Wang said, there are still problems involving the
illegal use of forests, particularly by cutting and selling its
timber.
</P>
<P>
Wang warned that the country's financial spending on forestry
was far from enough.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the legal system to provide more legislation
to protect the rights and interests of forest growers and
managers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
