<HEADLINE> Uganda Milk Exported to Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has begun to export milk
to the neighboring Rwanda, the daily paper, "The New Vision"
reported today
</P>
<P>
"Hundreds of liters of milk are exported from south-western
Uganda to Rwanda everyday," said Paul Kibwakari and William
Karekyezi, businessmen in Katuna, south-western Uganda.
</P>
<P>
According to the businessmen, the milk is unprocessed and
transported in aluminium cans.
</P>
<P>
The milk is sold on the local market at 300 Uganda Shillings a
liter but on an equevelent of 500 to 600 Uganda shillings in
Kigali.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers in south-western Mbarara and western Busheni
districts blamed local milk processors for delay payments at
times for their milk. 
</P>
