<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The German parliament today debated a
law to regulate the donation of body organs for transplanting,
focusing on whether removal of organs must get the signed
agreement of the donor before the person's death.
</P>
<P>
In Germany, family members can decide whether to donate organs
of a deceased person or not.
</P>
<P>
The issue has caused division in the Bundestag (the lower
house), with the 672 deputies asked by party leaders to vote based
on their conscience instead of any party line. 
