<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Adopts Laws On Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Polluters will be under attack in
east China's Fujian province after the Standing Committee of the
Provincial People's Congress there adopted laws recently on the
environmental protection of its capital, Fuzhou.
</P>
<P>
Government departments in the coastal city are required to work
out economic and social development plans in the light of
environmental protection. Funds for environmental protection
should be increased on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Licenses are needed for enterprises to discharge waste, and
fees will be imposed on those which do so.
</P>
<P>
Polluting enterprises will be banned in the vicinity of
residential quarters, cultural and educational zones, health
institutions, tourist areas, and nature protection zones.
</P>
<P>
Other measures will also be taken to reduce pollution in urban
and suburban areas. For one, drivers will not be allowed to blow
horns in down town areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
