<HEADLINE> Private Sector Booming in China's Hebei Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Statistics provided by the provincial bureau for industry and
commerce show that some six million people are now engaged in
private business while private companies have an added payroll of
more than one million in 1996 alone.
</P>
<P>
Total output value produced by self-employed business people
and private firms last year reached 61.5 billion yuan (about 7.4
billion US dollars), a surge of 56.1 percent over the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, the number of private companies with
registered capital volumes in excess of one million yuan each has
been found to total more than 1,500 in Hebei.
</P>
<P>
In some villages and townships, the private sector has become a
major part of the local economy and an important source of local
fiscal revenues, an official said.
</P>
<P>
A trend of building economies of scale was apparent in Hebei's
private sector, the official said, and he added that the private
sector contributes more than 70 percent of local taxes in two
counties and over 40 percent in 16 counties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
