<HEADLINE> Audi Sales Up 13 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Volkswagen's car division Audi saw a
nearly 13 percent increase in car sales in the first half of this
year, enjoying a strong start and expecting further rise in
earnings, the company said today.
</P>
<P>
Audi deputy chairman Franz-Josef Paefgen told shareholders in
Ingolstadt that turnover in the first half of this year would reach
10.8 billion marks (6.28 billion U.S. dollars) on sales of 277,000 cars,
up 16 percent from that of the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
He said Audi is expected to boost sales revenues this year by
about 19 percent to total 20 billion marks, with car sales
increasing to over 500,000, compared with 492,000 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Audi's pre-tax profit was 862 million marks, up 47
percent from 1995. 
