<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Foreign Trade Increases in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's foreign trade in this year
has reached 9.633 billion U.S. dollars by the end of June, with
exports posting 4.1 billion dollars, up 30.2 percent over the same
period of last year, local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The imports stood at 5.5 billion dollars, a slight increase of
0.3 percent, with consumer goods imports at 580 million dollars,
down 11.2 percent, compared to the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises contributed 1.147-billion-dollar
imports, up by 13.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the import surplus stood at 1.433 billion
dollars, compared to 1.77 billion dollars in the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that the country's foreign trade in the second
half of the year would achieve 12.767 billion dollars, with
5.1-billion-dollar exports and 7.667-billion-dollar imports.
</P>
</TEXT>
