<HEADLINE> Australian FM To Meet Chinese FM In Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Australian Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer said here today he was scheduled to meet Chinese
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen during his visit to Hong Kong from
June 29 to July 2.
</P>
<P>
The Australian foreign minister said he will also meet Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region Chief Executive Tung Chee-Hwa.
</P>
<P>
"I will underline the nature of Australia's interests in Hong
Kong," Downer said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Downer is to represent Australia at the ceremonies marking the
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong by China.
</P>
<P>
"It is important that Australia participate in these
ceremonies, to underline our support for the new Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region at this important time," the foreign
minister said.
</P>
<P>
Australia has an enduring stake in the future of Hong Kong,
which is home to over 30,000 Australians, and which is Australia's
ninth largest export market.
</P>
<P>
"I think Hong Kong has a bright future. I think it has a
successful future" after the handover on July 1, the foreign
minister said Tuesday in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
During his Hong Kong visit, Downer said he will also meet
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook and a number of his
counterparts from regional countries, who will be in Hong Kong to
attend the handover ceremonies.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister will start his four-day Vietnam visit on
July 2, followed by a two-day visit to the Lao People's Democratic
Republic.
</P>
<P>
Downer said he will meet a number of Vietnamese ministers and
follow up the outcome of the dialogue that has been developed
between Australia and Vietnam over the last year.
</P>
<P>
He said the dialogue includes key regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Prior to his Hong Kong visit, the foreign minister will visit
Luxembourg and Greece beginning June 25 and in Luxembourg he will
sign the Joint Declaration on Relations Between Australia and the
European Union on June 26.  
</P>
