<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 09:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Foils Largest Drug Smuggling Attempt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Jordan has smashed the largest ever
drug smuggling attempt, confiscating heroin and opium with an
estimated value of 6 million Jordanian dinars (about 8.5 million
U.S. dollars), a police source said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 47 kilograms of drugs, including 31 kilograms of
heroin and 16 kilograms of opium, were seized when five suspects
were trying to deliver them to neighboring counties last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Jordan Times today quoted Colonel Nazih
Shreideh, director of the Anti-Narcotics Department (AND) as
saying "This is the largest amount of drug seized in Jordan as
well as in the Arab world."
</P>
<P>
"We received tips from agents in neighboring countries and put
the suspects under surveillance (for 10 days), after they entered
Ramtha border and then arrested them at dawn Saturday while (they
were) attempting to deliver the drugs which came from Turkey," the
police official said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the suspects had hid the drugs in the petroleum
tank of a Mercedes 300 car, "which made it hard for border
inspectors to detect it."
</P>
<P>
The official did not disclose the destination of the drugs and
the identity of the five smugglers, only saying that they were
Arab and foreign nationals aged between 30 and 37.
</P>
<P>
The police official said that Jordan is a "defense line"
against the illegal trade since it is geographically situated
between drug producing and drug receiving countries.
</P>
<P>
"We know that most drug dealers use Jordan as a transit point,
but we want them to know that we will not allow any of these
smugglers to use Jordan as a base for drug smuggling." Shreideh
stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the department is in constant contact with the
authorities in neighboring countries in a joint effort to combat
drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Police statistics indicate that a total of 68 kilograms of
heroin and 43 kilograms of opium were seized in the kingdom last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
