<HEADLINE> 300 Overseas Chinese to Attend HK Handover Ceremony </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Three hundred overseas Chinese
have been invited as special guests to attend the Hong Kong
handover ceremony to be held at midnight on June 30, local sources
said here today.
</P>
<P>
An official with the China Travel Service (Hong Kong) Ltd.,
which is in charge of receiving these guests, said that they come
from more than 30 countries across the world, being either leaders
of local Chinese communities or renowned figures.
</P>
<P>
"The 300 people include business tycoons, social celebrities,
political figures, and personages with outstanding achievements in
the fields of science, technology and culture," said the official,
adding that they have all made great contributions to the
promotion of friendly relations between China and countries where
they live.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Hong Kong, these dignitaries will attend
the Sino-British Hong Kong handover ceremony, the inauguration
ceremony for the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (the Hong
Kong SAR) and the swearing-in of the Hong Kong SAR government, a
grand celebration and a reception marking the establishment of the
Hong Kong SAR, and a series of non-governmental celebrations.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of tens of million overseas Chinese all over the
world, they will bear witness to the historic event of Hong Kong's
return to China after it has been subjected to more than 150 years
of British colonial rule," the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said that these people are expected to arrive in Hong Kong
on 28th and 29th this month.  
</P>
