<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Home Ownership Plan Launched in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Finance Building Society (FBS) of
Zambia has launched a scheme to help local people acquire houses
easily.
</P>
<P>
The scheme known as "Home Savings Plan"is a two-stage option.
In the first one, the would-be home owner starts accumulating his
contribution toward the cost of the house by saving a regular
monthly sum.
</P>
<P>
In the second stage, one uses those savings together with a
housing loan from FBS to purchase a suitable house.
</P>
<P>
One will then have to pay month loan instalments but can get
tax relief on the loan interest.
</P>
<P>
The scheme will not only help people buy houses but also
assist them set money aside for other purposes like acquisition
of furniture, cars or child education.
</P>
<P>
The contribution should be regular for a minimum two years.
The savings will enjoy an attractive interest rate though the
rate may go up and down depending on changes in the country's
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Premature withdrawal will only be considered by way of
exemption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
