<HEADLINE> DPRK Calls for Setting UP New Peace Mechanism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- To mark 47th anniversary of the
outbreak of the Korean war, the official newspapers in the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) today repeated the
call for the establishment of a new peace mechanism to maintain
peace and stability in the Korean peninsula.
</P>
<P>
A Rodong Sinmun article said, "If the U.S. is truly desirous
of peace on the Korean peninsula it should implement the
DPRK-U.S. framework agreement with sincerity, thereby putting an
end to its hostile relations with the DPRK and replacing the
obsolete armistice agreement with a new peace mechanism."
</P>
<P>
"For the present, the U.S. should accede to the DPRK's
initiative for signing an interim agreement to that effect," it
said.
</P>
<P>
This is "the only way to bring undoubtful and durable peace to
the Korean peninsula," said the article.
</P>
<P>
The Korean people will certainly fulfill the wish for the
reunification of the fatherland, the article said.
</P>
<P>
The paper Minju Joson said that if the U.S. and the South
Korean ruling quarters persist in military confrontation with the
north, the DPRK will not mind the final battle with them.
</P>
<P>
The articles condemned the military reinforcements and
exercises by the United States and South Korea around the Korean
peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The Korean war broke out on June 25, 1950. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
