<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi Aims to Wash More Coal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi, a leading coal producer in
north China, aims to wash 40 percent of the coal it produces
by the year 2000. At present, only 20 percent of the coal coming
out of the province's mines is washed.
</P>
<P>
The province intends to ensure that more large coal dressing
plants, coking projects and high value-added coal projects will be
constructed. Meanwhile, the production capacity of existing coal
dressing plants will be optimized, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi will construct modern coal dressing plants close to its
major coal mines, near large centers of collection and
distribution, and in coal producing counties if transport
is convenient. Dressing increases the value of coal, changing it
from crude coal into "refined" coal.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, Shanxi has a coal reserve of 220
billion tons, and currently produces more than 300 million tons
a year. The figure constitutes a quarter of the country's output.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 million tons of coal produced by the province is
transported to other areas, making up 80 percent of the country's
total coal shipment volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
