<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Has no Arrears With IMF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has no arrears with the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) and it has the largest quota of
363.5 million special drawing rights (SDRs, with one SDR equaling
1.4 US dollars) with the IMF among the Common Market for Eastern
and Southern Africa countries.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by IMF resident representative Elwaleed Taha at
a recent economic seminar under the auspices of Bank of Zambia,
according to today's local press.
</P>
<P>
Taha said that the Zambian government's record since the
country embarked on the Structural Adjustment program in 1992 has
been excellent in terms of adhering to strong corrective economic
reform measures and, as a result of Zambia's strong commitment to
economic reforms, the country cleared its arrears in December
1995 and qualified for concessional lending from the IMF's
Enhanced Structural Adjustment Facility (ESAF).
</P>
<P>
The IMF disbursed 14 million US dollars of ESAF funds to
Zambia in March this year and this left a balance of 40 million
SDRs which will be disbursed in two equal instalments in the
remaining two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
