<HEADLINE> ROK Elevator Producer Eyes China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- LG Industrial Systems Co., the
largest elevator producer in the Republic of Korea (ROK), will
increase its investment volume in China to 140 million US dollars
by 2000 from the present 40 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
LG Industrial Systems regards China as extended home production
base because of its geological closeness to ROK as well as its
huge potential market, Bob Jang, executive vice-president of the
company's overseas operation told Xinhua just a week before the
China World Elevator Expo '97 to be held in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
He said his company will expand its sales volume in China to
6.5 billion yuan (780 million US dollars) by the year 2000,
snatching six percent of the total market. Last year, his company
sold China elevators worth 800 million yuan, accounting for only
one percent of the market.
</P>
<P>
Jang said that China, along with its sustained economic
development, will need more equipment related to the building of
office towers, hotels, apartments and power stations, and LG
Industrial Systems chooses to focus on developing the market of
elevators, power distributors, transformers and parking facilities
in the country.
</P>
<P>
LG Industrial Systems has established 27 sales centers in
China, accounting for 60 percent of the total worldwide. In July
this year, it will wind up the construction of an elevator joint
venture in Dalian in northeast China's Liaoning Province. Besides,
it plans to build five more factories in China before the year
2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
