<HEADLINE> Ramos Ratifies Philippines-HK Air Services Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
has ratified the Philippines-Hong Kong Air Services Agreement,
which was signed by the two sides on May 26 this year, the
presidential office said today.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement issued here, the office said that the
commercial air services between the Philippines and Hong Kong are
presently governed by the air services agreement between the
Philippines and the United Kingdom, but the Philippines-United
Kingdom pact will cease to apply to Hong Kong after June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The office quoted President Ramos as saying that air traffic
between the Philippines and Hong Kong has been growing during the
past years with approximately 1.7 million passengers in 1996, an
increase of 15 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
This agreement will "pave the way for the continued flourishing
of trade and tourism" between the Philippines and Hong Kong", he
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the presidential office, the agreement was
ratified by President Ramos on June 10.  
</P>
