<HEADLINE> S. Korea to Build Industrial Park in Siberia, Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 25 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and Russia have agreed
to build an exclusive industrial park for South Korean firms in
Nakhodka, Siberia.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached between a South Korean government
delegation and Russians in Moscow last week, according to
government sources here.
</P>
<P>
A formal accord will be signed during the conference of South
Korea-Russia Joint Committee on July 7-8, along with a land-lease
contract for 3.3 million square-meters, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
South Korean businessmen in the industrial complex will receive
favorable treatments, including a 50-percent cut in value-added
tax (VAT).
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to lower the current VAT rate of 20
percent to 10 percent for South Korean entrants in the park.
</P>
<P>
However, the firms would have to export 50 percent of their
production and the preferential customs and tax treatments would
only be applied to manufacturers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
