<HEADLINE> Hong Kong-Jiangsu Financial Cooperation Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Financial cooperation between Hong
Kong and Jiangsu Province, China's major economic powerhouse, has
expanded as the region is returning to the motherland in about a
week.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-funded enterprises in Jiangsu numbered 15,000 with a
total investment of 18.9 billion US dollars by the end of 1996,
accounting for 46 percent and 37 percent of the total overseas
businesses and investments, respectively, and ranking first in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investors have shifted their investment from
processing trades to hi-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has started 15 businesses in Hong Kong, with an
investment of 6.5 million US dollars, to attract overseas
investment through providing information and consulting and
promote direct trade.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises from Jiangsu like Yizheng Joint Corporation of
Chemical Fiber Industry and Panda Brand Electronics Enterprise
Group went public in Hong Kong. The H shares of Shanghai-Nanjing
expressway will be listed in Hong Kong soon.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong and Jiangsu are cooperating in other financial fields
like personnel training and exchange of managerial experience.
</P>
