<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Bank Warns Against Illegal Guarantee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- An official with the People's Bank
of China, the central bank, has urged stricter control over the
domestic institutions providing guarantee for economic activities
overseas.
</P>
<P>
He said that all government departments, local governments, and
public institutions are forbidden to provide guarantee for
economic activities overseas, except for relending overseas loans
with the State Council's approval.
</P>
<P>
Illegal guarantee provided by domestic institutions in some
areas has severely endangered state property and damaged China's
international credit, and even made it easy to make fraud, the
official explained.
</P>
<P>
All the guarantees for economic activities overseas have to be
done in strict accordance with the state guarantee law and related
regulations. Otherwise, such contracts will be invalidated, people
involved will be penalized or even brought to justice when they
are caught in extremely severe violations, the official warned.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
