<HEADLINE> Emergency Plan to Shift Asian Games Venues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Olympic Council of Asia
(OCA) will shift the venue for seven sports for next year's Asian
Games in Bangkok if construction work is not finished timely.
</P>
<P>
An OCA source said the governing body had identified existing
venues in southern Bangkok that could be used as the replacements.
</P>
<P>
According to the original plan, stadiums and press facilties in
the Bangkok Land complex in the northern part of the city must be
finished five months before the Games starts in December 1998.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jizhong, chairman of the Asian Games technical committee,
was concerned at the lack of progress at the B-Land site when he
visited the place in May, the source said.
</P>
<P>
And OCA committees have had to warn the authorities several
times about the pace of preparations.
</P>
<P>
B-Land is not only one of three main areas for the Asian Games,
but also the site of the main press centres and accommodation.
Sports for the complex include boxing, gymnastics, tennis,
weightlifting, billiards and snooker, rugby and volleyball.
</P>
