<HEADLINE> Private Sector Booming in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The private sector of the economy in
east China's Shandong Province has contributed 11 percent of its
total financial revenue.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the private and self-employed
businesses in the province increased their registered capital by
two billion and seven billion yuan in 1996, respectively up 17
percent and 57 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
A group of large-scale private enterprises have been built here
and effectively boosted the local economic development.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the number of private enterprises,
each with a registered capital of at least one million yuan,
exceeded 2,700, twice as many as the previous year. Ninety-eight
of them had a registered capital of well over 10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that private and self-employed businesses
in the province paid 2.69 billion yuan in taxes in 1996, up 9.3
percent over the previous year.  
</P>
