<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Second Annual ESAF Loan for Armenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) today announced the approval of a loan equivalent to 47
million U.S. dollars to back Armenia's economic program for 1997.
</P>
<P>
It is the second annual loan under the Enhanced Structural
Adjustment Facility (ESAF).
</P>
<P>
The loan is made available in two equal semiannual
installments, the first of which can be drawn on June 30 of this
year.
</P>
<P>
The major objectives of the 1997 economic program include:
achieving a real Gross Domestic Product (GDP) growth rate of about
six percent, bringing down the inflation rate during the year to
under 10 percent and increasing gross reserves to the equivalent
of 2.8 months of imports.
</P>
<P>
The ESAF is the IMF's concessional facility for assisting
eligible member states that are undertaking economic reform
programs. Its loans carry an interest rate of only 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Armenia joined the IMF in May 1992. Its quota is about 94
million dollars and its outstanding use of IMF financing currently
totals about 113 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
