<HEADLINE> Honduras to Reinforce Border Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Honduran Foreign Ministry
today suggested that the country's public security force step up
border control efforts to keep out armed Nicaraguans.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Delmer Urbizo Panting said dozens of Hondurans
had complained about attacks and robberies by re-armed Nicaraguan
guerrillas in some eastern border towns of Honduras.
</P>
