<HEADLINE> Child Pornography Suspects Arrested in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Italian police in Naples arrested 17
people today suspected of producing child pornography and of
trafficking those pornographic photos and videos.
</P>
<P>
Judiciary sources said the suspects are charged with enticing
the children to a garage and apartments where paedophiliac
materials were produced.
</P>
<P>
The investigation began a year ago after one of the 19
children's mother reported the case to police, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Magistrate Alfredo Ormanni said those children aged between six
and nine were subjected to violence in an elementary school and
continued later in apartments.
</P>
<P>
A school custodian among the 17 arrested was taken into custody
on the charge of providing information to the criminal ring about
those students with backgrounds of troubled families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
