<HEADLINE> One Killed, 34 Injured in U.S. Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 24 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 34
injured in an explosion in an aerosol packaging plant in northern
Indiana, this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Of the 34 injured, five were in serious conditions, reports
quoted sources from the Elkhart General Hospital as saying.
</P>
<P>
The explosion released a toxic gas which is used mainly for
sterilizing medical equipment. Some of the injured suffered from
respiratory distress caused by ethylene oxide.
</P>
<P>
Authorities evacuated a 1.5-kilometer radius around the plant.
</P>
