<HEADLINE> Japan to Grant Loan to Argentine Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Eximbank will loan
100 million U.S. dollars to small and medium-sized companies in
Argentina as their working capital.
</P>
<P>
Alieto Guadagni, Argentina's minister of industry, commerce and
mining, said the loan will be used for training programs for
Argentine industrialists in Japanese companies.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be lent over a period of five years at a rate of
around nine percent and will be available to small and
medium-sized companies who have annual turnovers of less than 20
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which will be signed this September during the annual
meeting of the International Monetary Fund, will enable Argentine
industrialists to receive technological and managerial training.
</P>
</TEXT>
