<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Eases Tariffs For Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Mexico has decided to resume a
trade agreement to reduce tariffs on Honduran exports, a Honduran
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Sergio Nunez, Honduras' deputy trade minister, said the
one-year reduction plan, which takes effect on July 1, will be
signed this week by Mexican finance and trade officials.
</P>
<P>
"This is so favorable that it will mean tariffs will be lowered
on some 900 products that Honduras is currently exporting to
Mexico," Nunez said.
</P>
<P>
Under the trade agreement, Mexican exports to Honduras,
especially food products, will receive the same preferential
treatment from Honduras. 
</P>
</TEXT>
