<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Kill Three Policemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels Tuesday
killed three policemen and wounded two others in an attack on a
police post in a fishing village in Eastern Province, according to
reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Police repulsed the attack, killing at least two rebels and
wounding a number of others, the reports said, quoting
eyewitnesses.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, dressed as fishermen, used automatic rifles and
grenades during the attack on the police post at Eravur, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a 14-year guerrilla war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country.
</P>
