<HEADLINE> Bonded Warehouse Operational in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The bonded warehouse in the
capital's economic and technological development zone has gone
into operation, as a major step to improve the climate for
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
According to the municipal source, the warehouse serves the
special purpose of storing raw materials needed by processing
enterprises and overseas-funded firms. It will also keep transship
goods as well as those permitted by the customs.
</P>
<P>
The warehouse, covering a total floor space of 4,200 sq m, will
make it convenient to overseas-funded firms and processing
enterprises and promote the city's foreign trade, the local source
said.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Economic and Technological Development Zone was set
up in 1992. So far, a total of 108 overseas-funded enterprises
have been established there and 30 of them are now operational.
</P>
<P>
The zone chalked up a turnover of two billion yuan in 1996,
gained 37 million US dollars through export, and delivered over
139 million yuan in tax.  
</P>
</TEXT>
