<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Return to China Example for World Peace: Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 24 (Xinhua) -- China's solution to the Hong
Kong issue will serve as an example for solving problems that
at one time jeopardize world peace, a senior Mexican legislator
said today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government's concept of "one country, two systems"
is a wise formula, said Augusto Gomez Villanueva, chairman of the
International Relations Committee of Mexico's Chamber of Deputies.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to China on coming July 1 is no doubt
an event of great significance not only for the Chinese, but also
for all mankind, Villanueva told Xinhua in an interview here.
</P>
<P>
By resuming the exercise of sovereignty, he said, the Chinese
leadership shows great wisdom in combining creativity and peace
with the firm enforcement of the principle of self-determination.
</P>
<P>
China will give the world an example of its force as a
sovereign nation and the way in which it will consolidate its
liberation and independence, the Mexican legislator said.
</P>
<P>
"There is no doubt whatsoever that Hong Kong's return ... is an
example of the most important expression of oriental force."
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that Hong Kong has always been and will
maintain its position as a world trade and financial center after
the Chinese government resumes the exercise of sovereignty there.
</P>
</TEXT>
