<HEADLINE> HK New World Group Expands Presence in Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong business group has
decided to funnel an additional six billion yuan into
infrastructure facilities, real estate, industry, tourism and the
development of high technologies in Wuhan, capital of central
China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong New World Group (HKNWG) has signed a contract
with this city for the second phase of economic cooperation on the
basis of previous fine cooperation, which is expected to roll up a
combined investment of 20 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that the HKNWG started comprehensive
cooperation with Wuhan in 1993 and, by the end of 1996, the HK
group had invested a total of three billion yuan, representing the
largest investor in the city.
</P>
<P>
During the first phase of cooperation, the New World Group
focused on the city's infrastructure facilities, revamping of
existing industrial enterprises, the second Yangtze River Bridge,
the Tianhe Airport and a comfortable housing project.
</P>
<P>
The sources have revealed that in the second phase HKNWG will
give priority to comfortable and affordable housing projects and
reconstruction of the Wuhan Hotel, as well as roads, bridges,
ports and energy projects. 
</P>
