<HEADLINE> Reynolds Runs Second Fastest Time over 400m </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- American Butch Reynolds ran the
second fastest time over 400 meters this year by clocking 44.45
seconds in an athletics meeting in Luzern of Switzerland Tuesday
night.
</P>
<P>
World record holder Reynolds finished ahead of compatriot Deon
Minor and Britain's Jamie Baulch.
</P>
<P>
Less known American Kenneth Brokenburr timed 10.11 seconds to
win the 100 meters event, beating second-placed compatriot Vincent
Henderson by 0.15 seconds.
</P>
<P>
American Tony Dees won the 110 meters hurdles in a time of
13.46 seconds, 0.09 ahead of Britain's Colin Jackson who placed
second.
</P>
