<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agrochemical Sector Co-operation Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Senior chemical industry officials
reaffirmed their determination to improve international
co-operation in the agrochemical sector, according to today's
"China Daily".
</P>
<P>
Chemical Industry Minister Gu Xiulian urged foreign chemical
companies to bolster technology exchanges and expand economic
co-operation in the agrochemical industry with their Chinese
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Through joint effort, co-operation in technology, funds and
equipment, the agrochemical sector can be pushed into a new stage,
Gu said Tuesday at the opening ceremony of a two-day China
International Agrochemical Conference '97 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"We warmly welcome friends from all countries to establish
joint ventures and co-operate in various forms," said the
minister, adding that her ministry intends to create a better
investment environment and working conditions for foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
Li Yongwu, vice-minister of the chemical industry, said that
foreign co-operation in the agro-chemical sector holds an
important position in the ministry's Ninth Five-Year Plan
(1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
More than 30 of the ministry's 80 well-selected key projects
that seek foreign investment will involve the agrochemical
industry, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
To promote Sino-foreign co-operation in the agrochemical
sector, the ministry will take the following major measures:
</P>
<P>
Expand the sources of foreign funds utilization. During the
Ninth Five-Year Plan, the ministry, in addition to foreign
governmental loans, will make full use of foreign export credit
and commercial loans and absorb investment from big-name
transnational companies. Foreign investment will be encouraged to
flow toward new and high-tech projects, and projects located in
the central and western areas of the country.
</P>
<P>
Construct a number of key projects. China will build a number
of large chemical projects equipped with advanced
technology. Breakthroughs are anticipated in establishing joint
ventures producing farm pesticides, rubber products and compound
fertilizers. Foreign companies are invited to establish joint or
co-operative firms through technology transfer.
</P>
<P>
Introduce foreign advanced technology and equipment according
to State industrial policy. Efforts will be made to import
advanced technology and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Create a sound investment environment. During the Ninth
Five-Year Plan, a management network on the protection of chemical
industry intellectual property rights will be established and
administrative management will be enhanced to guarantee the
promulgation and implementation of regulations concerning
intellectual property rights protection.  
</P>
</TEXT>
