<HEADLINE> Austria, China Seek More Business Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Austria and China held a joint
business seminar here today to seek more cooperation between small
and medium-sized enterprises in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 officials and entrepreneurs attended the event,
which was sponsored by China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation and Austria's Ministry of Economics.
</P>
<P>
Chinese representatives talked about the investment environment
China has created for foreign investors, and the transfer of
foreign technology in China. Austrian delegates listed the
problems and opportunities Austrian investors have faced in China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese entrepreneurs took 100 cooperative proposals to the
seminar and Austrians dozens. 
</P>
