<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yanjing Brewery Enters Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The nation's biggest beer producer
is entering the stock market with an offer of 80 million A-shares,
according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The Yanjing Brewery Co Ltd will issue shares today in order to
raise 570 million yuan (68 million US dollars), the company
announced recently.
</P>
<P>
Stock in the Beijing-based company will be listed on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchange after the issuance is completed.
</P>
<P>
According to a prospectus, proceeds from the sale of shares
will be used to expand the company's annual beer producing
capacity from 600,000 tons to 800,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts said the companys' plan to raise its
production is based on the popularity of its products.
</P>
<P>
Market surveys found that Yanjing brand beer is the first
choice of beer drinkers in 35 of China's big cities.
</P>
<P>
Its production and sales, standing at 590,000 tons in 1996,
tops beer makers in China.
</P>
<P>
Today in Beijing, Yanjing beer, with 85 percent of the city's
beer market, can be seen in almost every restaurant. In Tianjin,
it has taken 25 percent of the market. Other northern Chinese
cities also report its popularity.
</P>
<P>
Hot sales of its beer has pushed the company's net profits to
jump to 143 million yuan last year from 67 million yuan in 1994.
</P>
<P>
These achievements have encouraged the company to increase its
annual capacity to one million tons by 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
