<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aldag Wins Stage in Tour of Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- German Rolf Aldag broke from the
field for a solo run to win a rainy eighth stage on Tuesday in the
Tour of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Christophe Agnolutto cruised home in the 22nd place to maintain
a comfortable five minutes 14 second overall lead.
</P>
<P>
With two stages remaining, Agnolutto was on the brink to become
the first Frenchman since 1935 to win the event.
</P>
<P>
Against a steady downpour, Aldag finished the 174-kilometer
course in four hours seven minutes 19 seconds, beating compatriot
Udo Boelts by 57 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Dutchman Leon Van Bon was third a further four seconds adrift.
</P>
<P>
Aldag, a double stage winner at the Tour of Romandie earlier
this year, earned his third win of the season when he attacked and
dropped five breakaway partners with about 25km to go.
</P>
<P>
In the overall standings, Agnolutto who finihed 1:57 behind the
winner, did not surrender any time to his nearest challenger Oskar
Camenzind of Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
