<HEADLINE> Boardman Enjoys Bigger Lead in Tour of Catalonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Chris Boardman enjoyed a bigger
overall lead after a third-place finish on Tuesday in the sixth
stage of the Tour of Catalonia.
</P>
<P>
Boardman, a time-trial specialist, showed his strength against
the climbers by finishing third, just nine seconds behind winner
Fernando Escartin of Spain.
</P>
<P>
With other challengers stumbled, Escartin moved into second
place overall, one minute 36 seconds behind the British rider.
</P>
<P>
The 160-km stage had proved largely uneventful until the tough
four-km climb to the finish.
</P>
<P>
Boardman kept with the pace as a series of riders attempted to
break for the line, while Escartin, a mountain expert, finally got
clear of the pack.
</P>
<P>
The 237-km leg between Gerona and Pal, in the mountain state of
Andorra, is the toughest of the race and is the last realistic
chance for Boardman's challengers to deny him overall victory.
</P>
</TEXT>
