<HEADLINE> 70 Injured in Austrian Train Smash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 24 (Xinhua) -- About 70 people were injured this
afternoon, 10 of them seriously, when two passenger trains
collided in Austria's northwestern state of Upper Austria.
</P>
<P>
Austria's national news agency, APA, said the accident occurred
on a single track line near the Danube, and most of the passengers
were middle school students.
</P>
<P>
The wounded were flown to nearby hospitals by three
helicopters. Railway authorities speculate that the accident was
caused by human error on the part of drivers or station personnel.
</P>
<P>
Investigation on the cause of the accident is underway. 
</P>
