<HEADLINE> Suns Guard Kevin Johnson to Return for 1997-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 24 (Xinhua) - Phoenix point guard Kevin
Johnson has thought twice and will return to play for the Suns in
1997-98 after previously announcing his retirement from the NBA.
</P>
<P>
Johnson and Suns president Jerry Colangelo made the
announcement at a news conference Tuesday at America West Arena.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Johnson said at the beginning of the 1996-97
season that it would be his last. He repeated his intentions
several times during the season but admitted it would be tough to
walk away after 10 years.
</P>
<P>
A three-time All-Star whose career has been plagued by nagging
injuries, Johnson missed 12 games last season but led the Suns
with 20.1 points and 9.3 assists per game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
