<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host CAD Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The first China CAD Application
Engineering Fair is scheduled for July 7-10 at the Beijing
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the State Science and Technology Commission (SSTC)
and four other departments under the State Council, the fair is
aimed at promoting development and application of CAD technology.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 CAD software and hardware suppliers from at home
and abroad and 44 delegations from 32 provinces and municipalities
are expected to participate in the fair.
</P>
<P>
"China's CAD technology application and engineering, although
developing rapidly in recent years, still lag behind the world's
advanced level," said Shi Dinghuan, a SSTC official.
</P>
<P>
During the Eight Five-Year Plan (1991-95), the annual
production value of domestic CAD support and application software
amounted to 100 million yuan (12.5 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
More than 80 percent of the country's building and engineering
sectors have introduced CAD technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
