<HEADLINE> US Sprint Sensation Wins First Outing in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 24 (Xinhua) -- American sprint sensation Marion
Jones won her first outing race in Europe by clocking 11.08
seconds in the 100 meters at the Italian city Turin on Tuesday .
</P>
<P>
Jones postered a 2.8-meter per second tail wind in beating
Russia's Natalia Voronova into second place with 11.20 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Jones, who has run the three fastest 100-meter times in the
world so far this season and also earned the women's long jump
title at the recent US championships, is set to compete in both of
the events in the World Athletic Championships in August. 
</P>
