<HEADLINE> Antitank Missile Seized In Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Police agents confiscated an
antitank missile and detained five people in a house in Maracay,
capital of the northern state of Aragua, Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The explosive device, half-buried, was found during a raid on a
dwelling in which drugs were supposedly being sold, according
to press reports today quoting the Intelligence and Prevention
Service Divsion authorities.
</P>
<P>
The explosive device is presumed to belong to the Venezuelan
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
A group of DISIP specialists removed the missile after
verifying that it was deactivated. 
</P>
