<HEADLINE> Heynckes Signs for Real Madrid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 24 (Xinhua) -- German coach Jupp Heynckes signed a
two-year contract with newly-crowned Spanish champions Real Madrid
on Tuesday, replacing Fabio Capello who has returned to AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
Heynckes, formerly at Athletic Bilbao, took unfancied Tenerife
to the semi-finals of the UEFA Cup this season and his record has
impressed Real president Lorenzo Sanz who said he would give more
details of the signing when Heynckes was officially presented on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In other developments, Atletico Madrid coach Radomir Antic has
signed a new contract which will keep him at the Vicente Calderon
stadium until the end of next season.
</P>
<P>
Antic took Atletico to the League and Cup doubles a year ago
but this season they could only managed fifth place in the
league. 
</P>
