<HEADLINE> New Athens Airport to Be Completed in 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- A new international airport being
built for Athens in Spata would be completed in February 2001, a
Greek minister announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after an inspection of the airport site,
Public Works, Town Planning and Environment Minister Costas
Laliotis said that construction in several sectors was well ahead
of schedule.
</P>
<P>
He expressed satisfaction over progress made in the project,
saying that the organization and supervision of work by
engineering contractor Hochtief of Germany was "impressive."
</P>
<P>
The new airport, budgeted at 658 billion drachmas (about 2.53
billion U.S. dollars), is one of the biggest construction projects
under way in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The new facility will reportedly handle up to 16 million
passengers annually and around 600 flights daily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
