<DOCNO> XIE19970625.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine President Ends Visit to Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
left here for home today after paying a three-day official visit
to Greece.
</P>
<P>
During his visit here, the first by a Philippine head of state,
President Ramos held talks with his Greek counterpart, Costis
Stephanopoulos, Prime Minister Costas Simitis and other business
leaders on bilateral ties, the situation in the Balkans, Southeast
Europe and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Both sides stressed the need to expand bilateral cooperation in
the fields of commerce, shipbuilding and investment.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine delegation also signed a cooperation agreement
with the Greek side.
</P>
<P>
Ramos arrived here Sunday. Greece was the last leg of his
three-nation trip which also took him to Britain and Oman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
